description: Try our easy to follow Prehistoric Pies recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.

name: Prehistoric Pies Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Heat 1 tbs olive oil in a frying pan over high heat. Add 500g chicken mince and cook for 5 minutes, breaking up with a wooden spoon. Add 1 medium, finely chopped onion, 2 grated carrots, 125g can drained corn kernels and 1/2 cup frozen peas. Cook for 5 minutes until mince is cooked through. Sprinkle over 1 tbs plain flour, stir well for 1 minute. Add 1 cup chicken stock and 1/4 cup chopped parsley. Simmer until thickened. Set aside to cool.

Preheat oven to 200Â°C. Line two large baking trays with baking paper. Partially thaw 8 sheets frozen puff pastry. Working with 2 sheets at a time (keep remainder chilled), use a 12cm-diameter cutter (or small plate) to cut 4 rounds from each sheet. Reserve scraps (for recipe, left).

Place a heaped tablespoon of cooled filling mixture onto each pastry round. Fold in half and press edges together to seal. Lay on their sides and cut the edges in a zig-zag pattern to resemble spines on the back of a dinosaur. Place onto baking tray with spines upright. Repeat with remaining pastry and filling. Bake for 20-25 minutes until golden.
